****STORY 📕TIME****

I wanna share a story that just happened.  I usually always try and be a good person and help others. 

I was at a Supermarket just now in line to pay for my items and next to me was another cashier - I overheard her telling a little old lady about maybe in her late 70’s, “You don’t have enough money $ you will need to take some items back!”. As I hear this my heart drops and I ask the cashier “How much is she short ? She says about $23 dollars.  I told her put your items back I’ll pay the rest.  As I approached the little old lady she had tears in her eyes asking me if I’m Santa Claus (she might be saying that because I’m a bit fluffy right now lol She continues asking for God to Bless me 10x (not crying there is something in my eye!). 

She gives me the crumbled money she has in her hand which I immediately return to her, so I ended up paying for everything. 

It felt so good to help someone in need and this is why I am sharing this story.  I have always taught my kids to always help others. If they can and I have done this for years I never post about it because if you do something we should do it without seeking applause from everyone- However, I’m posting because after she ran after me and told me I made her day…I thought maybe my story can I inspire someone else to help someone and PAY IT FORWARD!!!

I hope everyone is having a blessed day stay safe everyone!!!

#stayblessed😇 #payitforward #bekind #godisgoodallthetime #storytime #feelsgoodtohelpothers❤#imnotcryingyourecrying

What are the benefits of seeing a Chiropractor/Physical Therapist after an accident?

Chiropractic manipulations can help your body to release an anti-inflammatory chemical that reduces internal swelling and pain and promotes healing. It is largely a combination of inflammation and pain that causes the loss of mobility in our back and neck after a car accident.

Physical therapy can help car accident victims increase their strength, improve their flexibility, and subsequently keep pain symptoms at bay.
